        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 12:49PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1249 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Meeman Shelby Forest State Park, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bartlett, Millington, Meeman Shelby Forest State Park, Memphis,
Lakeland, Ellendale, Dixonville, Frayser, Atoka, Griffin Corner,
Gammon, Quito, Woodstock, St Clair, Locke, Sloanville, Brunswick,
Raleigh, Wilkinsville, and Spring Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
